subject: How t test the object list
msgSnippet: Hi, I am testing the call to a function using easyMock where one of the parameter to it is the list of object. I am registering the expeted call with the list
messageBody:
Hi,
I am testing the call to a function using easyMock where one of the parameter to it is the list of object.
I am registering the expeted call with the list which will have the instance of objects.
But when the actual call is made then the function is receiving the list with the instance of object but both the list will not not have the same object instance.
Because of that it is giving the exception as below.

junit.framework.AssertionFailedError:
Unexpected method call
inject("VISTA", "F001203", <Name0><Key0>Value0</Key0></Name0><Name1><Key1>Value1</Key1></Name1><Name2><Key2>Value2</Key2></Name2><entrySystemData><scanDate>10/03/2005</scanDate><scanTime>12:15:25</scanTime><scanReferenceNumber>1000</scanReferenceNumber><archiveBox>fimsArchive</archiveBox><scanReferenceInfo>scanInfo</scanReferenceInfo></entrySystemData>, [123, 123, 123, 123]):
inject("VISTA", "F001203", <Name0><Key0>Value0</Key0></Name0><Name1><Key1>Value1</Key1></Name1><Name2><Key2>Value2</Key2></Name2><entrySystemData><scanDate>10/03/2005</scanDate><scanTime>12:15:25</scanTime><scanReferenceNumber>1000</scanReferenceNumber><archiveBox>fimsArchive</archiveBox><scanReferenceInfo>scanInfo</scanReferenceInfo></entrySystemData>, [123, 123, 123, 123]): expected: 0, actual: 1
inject("VISTA", "F001203", <Name0><Key0>Value0</Key0></Name0><Name1><Key1>Value1</Key1></Name1><Name2><Key2>Value2</Key2></Name2><entrySystemData><scanDate>10/03/2005</scanDate><scanTime>12:15:25</scanTime><scanReferenceNumber>1000</scanReferenceNumber><archiveBox>fimsArchive</archiveBox><scanReferenceInfo>scanInfo</scanReferenceInfo></entrySystemData>, [123, 123, 123, 123]): expected: 1, actual: 0

has anybody came across the same problem before. Or can anybody suggest some way to solve this problem.

Thanks in advance.

Saroj
